@userBaseUrl  = http://localhost:8081
@storeBaseUrl = http://localhost:8082
@orderBaseUrl = http://localhost:8083

# =============================================================================
# End-to-End Scenario
#
# Actors : 1 customer, 1 owner
# Flow   : signup → signin → create store+5 products → cart → order → sold
#          → price change (snapshot comparison) → monthly statistics
#
# Cart snapshot
#   product 1 (후라이드 치킨)  qty 2 × 18,000 = 36,000
#   product 2 (양념 치킨)      qty 1 × 19,000 = 19,000
#   product 3 (간장 치킨)      qty 1 × 20,000 = 20,000
#   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   order totalPrice (frozen)              = 75,000
#
# After the order is SOLD the owner raises product 1 to 22,000.
#   Same order at new price: 22,000×2 + 19,000 + 20,000 = 83,000
#   Existing order totalPrice stays at 75,000  → 8,000원 difference
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
# STEP 1 — Sign up
# =============================================================================

### [1-1] Sign up — CUSTOMER
POST {{userBaseUrl}}/api/users/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "mentee@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "010-1212-1212"
}

### [1-2] Sign up — OWNER
POST {{userBaseUrl}}/api/users/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "mentor@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "010-2323-2323",
  "role": "OWNER"
}


### =============================================================================
# STEP 2 — Sign in (tokens saved to global)
# =============================================================================

### [2-1] Sign in — CUSTOMER  →  saves customerToken
POST {{userBaseUrl}}/api/users/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "mentee@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
client.global.set("customerToken", "Bearer " + response.body.accessToken);
%}

### [2-2] Sign in — OWNER  →  saves ownerToken
POST {{userBaseUrl}}/api/users/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "mentor@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
client.global.set("ownerToken", "Bearer " + response.body.accessToken);
%}


### =============================================================================
# STEP 3 — Owner creates store
# =============================================================================

### [3-1] Create store  →  saves storeId
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "바삭 치킨집22",
  "address": "서울특별시 강남구 테헤란로 1",
  "phone": "02-1234-5678",
  "content": "신선한 재료로 만든 바삭한 치킨 전문점",
  "storePictureUrl": null,
  "productCreatedTime": 32400000,
  "openedTime": 36000000,
  "closedTime": 79200000,
  "closedDays": "MONDAY"
}

> {%
client.global.set("storeId", response.body.id);
%}

### Get my stores (OWNER)
GET {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/mine
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}

### =============================================================================
# STEP 4 — Owner creates 5 products
# =============================================================================

### [4-1] Create product 1 — 후라이드 치킨  18,000원  →  saves product1Id
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "후라이드 치킨",
  "description": "바삭하고 담백한 정통 후라이드 치킨",
  "price": 18000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

> {%
client.global.set("product1Id", response.body.id);
%}

### [4-2] Create product 2 — 양념 치킨  19,000원  →  saves product2Id
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "양념 치킨",
  "description": "달콤하고 매콤한 양념 치킨",
  "price": 19000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

> {%
client.global.set("product2Id", response.body.id);
%}

###

### [4-3] Create product 3 — 간장 치킨  20,000원  →  saves product3Id
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "간장 치킨",
  "description": "고소한 간장 소스의 치킨",
  "price": 20000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

> {%
client.global.set("product3Id", response.body.id);
%}

###

### [4-4] Create product 4 — 파닭  21,000원
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "파닭",
  "description": "파와 함께 즐기는 바삭한 치킨",
  "price": 21000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

### [4-5] Create product 5 — 순살 치킨  22,000원
POST {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "순살 치킨",
  "description": "뼈 없이 즐기는 부드러운 순살 치킨",
  "price": 22000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

### List products by store (public)
GET {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

### =============================================================================
# STEP 5 — Customer adds 3 products to cart (unit prices snapshotted here)
# =============================================================================

### [5-1] Add product 1  qty 2  →  unitPrice 18,000 snapshotted  →  saves cartId
POST {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": {{product1Id}},
  "quantity": 2
}

> {%
client.global.set("cartId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### [5-2] Add product 2  qty 1  →  unitPrice 19,000 snapshotted
POST {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": {{product2Id}},
  "quantity": 1
}

###

### [5-3] Add product 3  qty 1  →  unitPrice 20,000 snapshotted
POST {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": {{product3Id}},
  "quantity": 1
}

###

### [5-4] View cart — confirm items and snapshotted unit prices
# Expected: items[].unitPrice = [18000, 19000, 20000], totalPrice = 75000
GET {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/carts
Authorization: {{customerToken}}


# =============================================================================
# STEP 6 — Customer checks out  (cart → Order PENDING)
# =============================================================================

### [6-1] Checkout  →  saves orderId
PUT {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/carts/{{cartId}}/checkout
Authorization: {{customerToken}}

> {%
client.global.set("orderId", response.body.id);
%}


### =============================================================================
# STEP 7 — Owner views orders and marks as SOLD
# =============================================================================

### [7-1] Owner lists orders for store  →  confirm order status = PENDING
GET {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/orders
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}

###

### [7-2] Owner marks order SOLD  (product popularities incremented via internal call)
PUT {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/orders/{{orderId}}/sold
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}


# =============================================================================
# STEP 8 — Price change comparison
#
# Owner raises product 1 from 18,000 → 22,000 after the order is already SOLD.
# The existing order's totalPrice must stay at 75,000 (frozen snapshot).
#
# BEFORE  product 1 price : 18,000원
# AFTER   product 1 price : 22,000원  (+4,000)
#
# Order snapshot total   : 75,000원  (18,000×2 + 19,000 + 20,000)
# Re-order at new prices : 83,000원  (22,000×2 + 19,000 + 20,000)  → +8,000원
# =============================================================================

### [8-1] BEFORE — product 1 price: 18,000원
GET {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products/{{product1Id}}
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}

###

### [8-2] Owner raises product 1 price to 22,000원
PUT {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products/{{product1Id}}
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "후라이드 치킨",
  "description": "바삭하고 담백한 정통 후라이드 치킨",
  "price": 22000,
  "productPictureUrl": null
}

###

### [8-3] AFTER — product 1 price: 22,000원  (changed)
GET {{storeBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/products/{{product1Id}}
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}

###

### [8-4] Order snapshot — totalPrice still 75,000원  (frozen at purchase time)
# Proves unit prices were captured at add-to-cart time, not at current product price
GET {{orderBaseUrl}}/internal/orders/{{orderId}}


# =============================================================================
# STEP 9 — Monthly statistics
#
# Owner   revenue  : 75,000원
# Customer spending: 75,000원
# =============================================================================

### [9-1] Owner revenue — March 2026 (Seoul time)
GET {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/stores/{{storeId}}/statistics/revenue?year=2026&month=3&timezone=Asia/Seoul
Authorization: {{ownerToken}}

###

### [9-2] Customer spending — March 2026 (Seoul time)
GET {{orderBaseUrl}}/api/users/me/statistics/spending?year=2026&month=3&timezone=Asia/Seoul
Authorization: {{customerToken}}
